<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1905,2002]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,151,573]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="429" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[324,426,1905,1930]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1121,1144]" captionTargetBox="[161,1413,209,1090]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[150,1436,193,1101]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–11. Stevenia gilasiani sp. nov.. 6–8. Holotype ♂. 6. Detail of thorax, showing two postpronotal setae. 7. Abdomen in dorsal view. 8. Abdomen in lateral view, showing the sexual-patches on tergites 3 and 4. 9–11. Details of cuticle and setae composing the sexual-patches, using scanning electron microscopy (SEM) (paratype, MZUR). 9. Sexual-patches of tergite 3 in ventral view. 10. Seta and porous area. 11. Internal surface of cuticle at of the base of a seta composing a sexualpatch, showing the sieve-like structure at level of porous area." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612663/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Figs 7–8</figureCitation>
). Mid-dorsal depression of syntergite 1+2 confined to anterior 1/4 of syntergite. Syntergite 1+2 without median marginal setae, with several lateral discal and lateral marginal setae. Tergite 3 with one pair of median marginal setae, one pair of lateral discal setae and two pairs of lateral marginal setae. Tergites 4 and 5 each with a row of marginal setae and without discal setae. Tergite 5 very short, approximately 1/3 length of tergite 4. Sternite 4 exposed. Ventral sides of tergites 3, 4 and 5 with paired patches of appressed setae and cuticular microsculpture (i.e., sexual-patches) (
<figureCitation box="[571,685,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1121,1144]" captionTargetBox="[161,1413,209,1090]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[150,1436,193,1101]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–11. Stevenia gilasiani sp. nov.. 6–8. Holotype ♂. 6. Detail of thorax, showing two postpronotal setae. 7. Abdomen in dorsal view. 8. Abdomen in lateral view, showing the sexual-patches on tergites 3 and 4. 9–11. Details of cuticle and setae composing the sexual-patches, using scanning electron microscopy (SEM) (paratype, MZUR). 9. Sexual-patches of tergite 3 in ventral view. 10. Seta and porous area. 11. Internal surface of cuticle at of the base of a seta composing a sexualpatch, showing the sieve-like structure at level of porous area." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612663/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="429">Figs 8–11</figureCitation>
). Sexual-patches also present on sternites 3 and 4. 
<emphasis box="[1250,1372,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="429">Terminalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 12–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1777,1800]" captionTargetBox="[245,1340,379,1725]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[209,1378,348,1756]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–14. Stevenia gilasiani Ziegler, Gisondi &amp; Cerretti, sp. nov., terminalia (paratype, MZUR). 12. Lateral view. 13. Dorsolateral view. 14. Detail of the terminalia in ventral view. Abbreviations: aj = ejaculatory apodeme; app = phallus apodeme; c = cerci; ep = epandrium; hyp = hypandrium; pr = pregonite; ps = postgonite; s = surstylus; sd = sperm ducts." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612665/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="429">Figs 12–14</figureCitation>
). Epandrium short and convex. Cercus with curled cuticular microsculpture, long setae on lateral surface and one pair of long setae on apical dorsal surface; cerci approximately 2/3 of length of surstylus, with a dorsomedial suture separating them. Surstylus dagger-like in lateral view and rounded at apex in posterior view, twisted inward (
<figureCitation box="[159,291,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1777,1800]" captionTargetBox="[245,1340,379,1725]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[209,1378,348,1756]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–14. Stevenia gilasiani Ziegler, Gisondi &amp; Cerretti, sp. nov., terminalia (paratype, MZUR). 12. Lateral view. 13. Dorsolateral view. 14. Detail of the terminalia in ventral view. Abbreviations: aj = ejaculatory apodeme; app = phallus apodeme; c = cerci; ep = epandrium; hyp = hypandrium; pr = pregonite; ps = postgonite; s = surstylus; sd = sperm ducts." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612665/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="429">Figs 12–13</figureCitation>
). Processus longus stick-like and firmly fused to base of surstylus. Distiphallus as long as surstylus; lateroventral face of distiphallus sclerotized and covered with scale-like spinules. Acrophallus with tripartite sperm duct (
<figureCitation box="[214,298,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1777,1800]" captionTargetBox="[245,1340,379,1725]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[209,1378,348,1756]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–14. Stevenia gilasiani Ziegler, Gisondi &amp; Cerretti, sp. nov., terminalia (paratype, MZUR). 12. Lateral view. 13. Dorsolateral view. 14. Detail of the terminalia in ventral view. Abbreviations: aj = ejaculatory apodeme; app = phallus apodeme; c = cerci; ep = epandrium; hyp = hypandrium; pr = pregonite; ps = postgonite; s = surstylus; sd = sperm ducts." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612665/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="429">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
